.TH LPF-ROLLBACK 8 "June 2026" "lpf 0.2.1" "lpf Manual"
.SH NAME
lpf\-rollback \- restore a previous known\-good policy state
.SH SYNOPSIS
lpf rollback [policy\-id]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Restore a previous lpf policy state and backend preimages.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-\-now
rollback the active guarded apply immediately
.SH EXAMPLES
lpf rollback
lpf rollback 2026\-06\-16T20:30:00Z
.SH FILES
/etc/lpf.conf
/var/lib/lpf/history
/var/lib/lpf/rollback
.SH SAFETY NOTES
Rollback must cover nftables, routes, tc, dynamic tables, and owned sysctls.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success.
Non\-zero when validation, planning, or host operations fail.
.SH SEE ALSO
lpf\-apply(8), lpf\-history(8)
